verbs.description: unstock (third-person singular simple present unstocks, present participle unstocking, simple past and past participle unstocked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove the stock (supply of goods) from; to empty of goods.
examples: One I met during the inspections of freezer rooms indicated that her principal function was the stocking and unstocking of the freezer room at a very large supermarket.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove the stock (block or support) from; to release from that which fixes in place.
(transitive) To remove (a ship etc.) from the stocks.
